The sum of the exterior angles of any polygon is $360^\circ.$  Since the heptagon is regular, each exterior angle of the heptagon has measure $\frac{360^\circ}{7}.$  Therefore, the exterior angle of the heptagon at $D$ has measure $\frac{360^\circ}{7},$ and the exterior angle of the square at $D$ has measure $90^\circ.$

