Therefore, the exterior angle of the heptagon at $C$ has measure $180^\circ - \frac{360^\circ}{7}.$  Then
\[\angle BAC = \angle CAD + \angle CAB = 90^\circ - \left( 180^\circ - \frac{360^\circ}{7} \right) = \boxed{\frac{90^\circ}{7}}.\]
